00;font-weight:700;font-size:12pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:\"Calibri\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h5{padding-top:11pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:11pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:\"Calibri\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h6{padding-top:10pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:10pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:\"Calibri\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}</style></head><body class=\"c6\"><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Dear users of CASHBOX Wallet APP: We have updated the </span><span class=\"c3\">User Privacy Policy of CASHBOX Wallet APP</span><span class=\"c1\">. This version of the </span><span class=\"c3\">User Privacy Policy of CASHBOX Wallet APP</span><span class=\"c1\">&nbsp;will explain, on a case-by-case basis, the purpose, scope and manner in which each feature may collect personal information; how we protect your personal information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Update time: May 7, 2020</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>[Special Notes]</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>Please read the </span><span class=\"c3\">User Privacy Policy of CASHBOX Wallet APP </span><span class=\"c1\">(especially the bold underlined content) carefully to learn more about how we collect, use and save information, and be sure to understand our rules on how to handle your personal information, so that you can make an appropriate choice about our services. The relevant terms in this Privacy Policy will be expressed as concisely as possible so that you can better understand them. By using or continuing to use our products and/or services after we update this Privacy Policy (we will promptly inform you of the updates), you agree to the content of this Privacy Policy (including the updated version) and agree that we will collect, use, save and share your relevant information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">If you have any questions during the reading, feel free to email us at:</span><span class=\"c1 c5\">&nbsp;CASHBOX@scry.info</span><span class=\"c1\">. You should stop using the CASHBOX Wallet APP immediately if you do not agree with any of the terms in the policy.</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>Introduction</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">CASHBOX Wallet App values user information security and privacy protection, and does its utmost to prevent your information from being leaked, damaged, or lost through reasonable and effective information security technology and management processes; provides you with convenient information management options to enhance your convenience of information management; protects your communication secrets, and protects your information and communication security. CASHBOX Wallet APP strictly complies with laws and regulations, only collects necessary information, and improves the transparency of information processing. In every link of product or service development, it integrates law, product, design and other factors with the concept of privacy protection to provide you with more secure and reliable services.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">We formulate and follow the </span><span class=\"c3\">User Privacy Policy of CASHBOX Wallet APP</span><span class=\"c1\">&nbsp;(hereinafter referred to as &quot;the Policy&quot;), which mainly explains the following to you:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; What information do we collect;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; What do we use the information for;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; How do we share, transfer, and publicly disclose your personal information;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; How do we save your personal information;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; How do you manage personal information;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; Protection of minors&#39; personal information</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; Notification and revision</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">&bull; How to contact us</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c4\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">I. Definition and Scope of Personal Information</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Unless otherwise agreed, the terms used in the Policy have the following definitions.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">1.1 Personal information: refers to all kinds of information recorded by electronic or other means that can identify the personal identity of a natural person individually or in combination with other information. The personal information involved in the Policy includes the name, nickname, date of birth, nationality, ID number, gender, age, personal biometric information, address, telephone number, company, institution, occupation of a natural person.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">1.2 Personal sensitive information: refers to personal information that, once leaked, illegally provided or abused, may endanger the safety of person and property, and easily lead to damage to personal reputation, physical and mental health or discriminatory treatment. For example, personal sensitive information includes ID number, personal biometric information, bank account number, communication content, health and physiological information, etc. Therefore, you should exercise your own discretion to determine the authenticity, legality and validity of the relevant digital assets and/or information, and bear the liabilities and losses arising therefrom.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><a id=\"id.gjdgxs\"></a><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">1.3 Anonymized information refers to information that is subject to technical processing of personal information so that the subject of personal information cannot be identified and cannot be recovered after processing, which is not included in personal information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">1.4 Other information that cannot be used to identify a specific natural person or reflect the activities of a specific natural person is not personal information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Except the above definitions, other terms used in the Policy have the same meaning as those used in the </span><span class=\"c3\">User Service Agreement of CASHBOX Wallet APP</span><span class=\"c1\">. Please do not hesitate to contact us with any questions.</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>II. Information We Collect</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">2.1 CASHBOX Wallet is a digital asset wallet based on blockchain, including other auxiliary tools developed to facilitate the use of the blockchain system. The personal information collected by CASHBOX Wallet APP includes:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">2.1.1 When you use or access the software, the software automatically receives and records the server values on the user&#39;s browser, including your device model, geographical location, IP address and other data, as well as the webpage records you request to access;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">2.1.2 The data collected by the software about your transactions on the platform, including the wallet address, transfer-in and transfer-out records you created and imported;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">2.1.3 Other personal information collected by the software will be clearly stated in a way to remind you and obtain your consent.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">2.2 We may obtain the information generated or shared when you use third-party partner services. This includes that: we will obtain your login name and time for the services from a third party partner, or login time to CASHBOX Wallet for your authorization management when you use the CASHBOX Wallet account to log into the third-party partner service, or you use the service account of the third-party partner to log into the CASHBOX Wallet. Please read the user agreement or privacy policy of the third-party partner service carefully.</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>III. How do we use the information we collect</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">We strictly abide by the provisions of laws and regulations and the agreement with users, and use the collected information for the following purposes. If we use your information beyond the following purposes, we will explain it to you again and obtain your consent.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">3.1 To provide you with services.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">3.2 To satisfy your individual needs, such as language settings, location settings, personalized help services.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">3.3 Product development and service optimization. For example, when our system fails, we will record and analyze the information generated when the system fails and optimize our services.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">3.4 Safety guarantee. For example, we will use your information for identity verification, security precautions, anti-fraud monitoring, archiving or backup, customer security services and other purposes. The security software you download or install may detect malicious programs or viruses, or identify fraudulent information for you.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">3.5 To evaluate and improve the effectiveness of our advertising and other promotional activities.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">3.6 To manage software, such as software certification and upgrading, etc.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">3.7 To invite you to participate in a survey about our services.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">In order to provide you with a better experience, improve our services or use them for other purposes you agree, we may use the information collected through certain services for our other services, subject to applicable laws and regulations. For example, the information generated when you use one of our services will be used in another service to show you personalized content or advertisements, and used for user research, analysis and statistics, etc. To secure the service and help us better understand how our application is performing, we may record relevant information, such as application usage frequency, failure information, overall usage, performance data, and source of the application. We do not combine the information we store in the analysis software with the personally identifiable information you provide in your application.</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>IV. How Do We Share, Transfer, and Publicly Disclose Your Information</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">4.1 We will comply with relevant laws and regulations and keep your personal information confidential. We will not share your personal information with others unless:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">A. Only by sharing your personal information can we provide the services you need.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">B. We may share your relevant information within our affiliates in order to improve the quality of our products and services or to provide you with new products and services.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">C. When you use any third-party service through the CASHBOX Wallet software, the CASHBOX Wallet will share your personal information with the third party providing the service as specified in the &quot;Collection of Personal Information&quot; clause.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">D. When assisting in the settlement of disputes or controversies involving you, we may provide the necessary information to the third party who has an interest with you, so as to safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of users.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">E. Necessary personal information obtained by a criminal investigation organ in order to investigate a crime by law, or necessary personal information obtained by an administrative organ or judicial organ in a manner prescribed by law and with your authorization.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">F. We provide information necessary to protect the public interest, property or safety, to the extent required or permitted by law.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">G. Your express consent or authorization is required separately.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">4.2 We will not provide your personal information for any third party organization or individual without legal procedures or your consent. We will sign strict confidentiality agreements with companies, organizations and individuals with whom we share personal information, and require them to process personal information in accordance with our instructions, the Privacy Policy and any other related confidentiality and security measures.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">4.3 We will comply with relevant laws and regulations and keep your personal information confidential. We will not publicly disclose your personal information unless we have your prior express consent or authorization or are required by law.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">4.4 In addition, according to applicable laws, regulations and national standards, we may share, transfer, and publicly disclose personal information in the following circumstances without prior authorization of the personal information subject:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">A. Those directly related to national security and national defense security;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">B. Those directly related to public safety, public health and major public interests;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">C. Those directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">D. Those out of protecting the lives, properties, important legal rights and interests of personal information subjects or other individuals which however, is difficult to obtain the consent of users;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">E. Personal information which is disclosed to the public by the subjects;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">F. If the personal information is collected from legally disclosed information, such as legal news reports and government information disclosure.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">4.5 In the event of any acquisition, merger, reorganization or other changes, we will require the changed entity to comply with the Privacy Policy and fulfill its original responsibilities and obligations. If the changed entity needs to change the purposes of using personal information, we will require the entity to obtain your express consent in advance. Internally, in the aforementioned acquisition and merger activities, the data managed by the acquired and merged objects (including user data) will be processed and protected using the same standards and requirements as the CASHBOX Wallet data.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c4\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">V. How Do We Protect Your Personal Information</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">We provide appropriate safety guarantee for your information to prevent the loss, misuse, unauthorized access or disclosure of information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">5.1 We strictly abide by laws and regulations to protect communication secrets of users.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">5.2 We will take a variety of security measures within a reasonable level of security to guarantee the security of information. For example, we use encryption techniques (e.g., TLS, SSL), anonymization, and other means to protect your personal information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">5.3 We set up specialized management systems, processes and organizations to ensure information security. For example, we strictly limit the number of people who access information and require them to perform confidentiality obligations and conduct reviews.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">5.4 In case of personal information leakage or other security incidents, we will initiate contingency plans to prevent the expansion of security incidents and notify you in the form of push notifications, announcements, etc.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">5.5 We will take all reasonable and feasible measures to ensure that irrelevant personal information is not collected. We will retain your personal information only for as long as it is necessary to achieve the purposes stated in the Privacy Policy, unless the retention period is extended or such retention is permitted by law.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">5.6 The Internet is not an absolutely secure environment, and it is not possible to determine whether communication methods with other users such as e-mail, instant messaging, social software, etc. are fully encrypted. We recommend that you use complex passwords when using such tools, and pay attention to protecting the security of your personal information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">5.7 The Internet environment is not 100% secure, and we will do our best to ensure or guarantee the security of any information you send to us. If our physical, technical, administrative or protective facilities are damaged, resulting in unauthorized access to information, public disclosure, manipulation, or destruction, as well as damage to your legitimate rights and interests, we will assume corresponding legal responsibility.</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>VI. How Do We Save Your Personal Information</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.1 We implement appropriate physical, electronic, administrative and technical measures to protect and safeguard your personal data. We endeavour to ensure that any personal data collected through our platform is free from interference from third parties not related to us. The security measures we take include but are not limited to:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.1.1 Physical measures: the records containing your personal data will be stored in a locked place.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.1.2 Electronic measures: computer data containing your personal data will be stored on computer systems and storage media subject to strict log-in restrictions.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.1.3 Management measures: we have set up relevant departments for the security protection of user information, established relevant internal control systems, and adopted strict authorization principles for staff who may have access to your information. Only our authorized staff will have access to your personal data and these staff will be subject to our internal code of conduct on the confidentiality of personal data. In addition, we constantly provide staff with trainings of relevant laws, regulations and privacy safety to strengthen their awareness of safety, and regularly organize internal relevant personnel to conduct emergency response trainings and emergency drills, so that they can master the post responsibilities and emergency response strategies and procedures</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.1.4 Technical measures: encryption technology such as Secure Socket Layer Encryption may be used to transfer your personal data.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.1.5 Security measures: to ensure the security of your information, we are committed to using a variety of current and general security technologies and supporting management systems to minimize the risks of information disclosure, damage, misuse, unauthorized access, unauthorized disclosure, and change. For example, the network security layer software (SSL) is used for transmission encryption, information encryption and storage, thus severely restricting access to the data center. When transmitting and storing personal sensitive information (including personal biometric information), we will adopt security measures such as encryption, permission control, de-identification and desensitization.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.1.6 Other measures: we will regularly review our procedures for the collection, storage and processing of personal data; restrict the access of our employees and suppliers to your data according to the necessary principles; and require our employees and suppliers to comply with strict contractual confidentiality obligations.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.2 If you are aware of any security vulnerabilities on our platform, please contact us immediately so that we can take appropriate action as soon as possible.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">6.3 Despite the implementation of the above technical and security measures, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of data transmission on the Internet, so we cannot absolutely guarantee that the personal information you provide to us through our platform will be secure at all times. We will update and publicize the security risk, assessment report on security impact of personal information and other relevant contents from time to time, which can be obtained through the announcement on this platform.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">VII. How Do You Manage Your Information</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">7.1 Create A Wallet</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">You must first create a wallet on the platform before using this software services. Individual users who create wallets shall be natural persons who have reached the age of 18 or have full civil rights and capacity for civil conduct in accordance with the laws of the country where they are located, and can independently assume civil liabilities; legal persons, organizations or other institutions that intend to create a wallet shall designate a representative office of a natural person who has reached the age of 18 or has full civil rights and capacity for civil conduct in accordance with the laws of the country where they are located, and can independently assume civil liabilities.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">7.2 Set wallet password, private key, mnemonic or Keystore</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Adhering to the decentralized features of blockchain and for the purpose of protecting the security of users&#39; digital tokens, this software provides decentralized services different from those provided by banking financial institutions. Therefore, you need to remember the wallet password (i.e. the password set by the user when creating/importing the wallet), private key, mnemonics or Keystore by yourself. We cannot provide you with the services such as retrieving the wallet password, private key, mnemonics or Keystore of users, freezing, reporting loss and recovering the wallet, or rolling back the transaction.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">7.3 Inquire, correct and delete your information</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">You have the right to inquire, correct or supplement your information. If any of your personal data is inaccurate, you can request to update your information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">You may request us to delete your personal information in the following circumstances:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">A. If our processing of personal information violates laws and regulations;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">B. If we collect and use your personal information without your express consent;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">C. If our processing of personal information seriously violates the agreement with you;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">D. If you no longer use our products or services, or you take the initiative to log out of the account;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">E. If we no longer provide you with products or services forever.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">If we decide to respond to your request for deletion, we will also notify the subjects who have obtained your personal information from us as far as possible, and request them to delete your information in time (unless otherwise provided by laws and regulations, or these subjects have independently obtained your authorization).</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">After you delete the relevant information on your own or with our assistance, we may not be able to immediately delete the corresponding information from the backup system due to applicable laws and security technologies, and we will securely store your personal information and isolate it from any further processing until the backup can be cleared or anonymized.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">7.4 Keep Your Information Safe</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">You must keep your mobile device containing CASHBOX Wallet, backup information of CASHBOX Wallet, wallet password backup, mnemonics, private key and Keystore. If you lose your mobile device, delete and fail to backup CASHBOX Wallet information, delete and fail to backup your wallet, have your wallet stolen, or forget wallet password, private key, mnemonics or Keystore, you cannot restore or retrieve your wallet password, private key, mnemonics, or Keystore based on the decentralized features of this service.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">7.5 Automatic decision of constrained information system</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">In some business functions, we may only make decisions based on non-manual automatic decision-making mechanisms including information systems, algorithms, etc. If these decisions significantly affect your legal rights and interests, you have the right to request an explanation from us, and we will also provide a method of appeal without prejudice to CASHBOX Wallet business secrets or other user rights and public interests.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">7.6 Respond to your above request</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">To ensure safety, you may need to provide a written request or otherwise prove your identity. We may ask you to verify your identity before processing your request.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">We will reply you within 15 days. You can also make a complaint through the customer service email in case of any dissatisfaction.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">We will not be able to respond to your request as required by laws and regulations under the following circumstances:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">A. Those related to national security and national defense security;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">B. Those related to public safety, public health and major public interests;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">C. Those related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">D. In case there is sufficient evidence that the subject of personal information is subjectively malicious or abuses the rights;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">E. In case responding to your request will cause serious damage to the legitimate rights and interests of you or other individuals or organizations;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">F. In case it involves trade secrets.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">VIII. Information You Share</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">8.1 You can share your relevant information with others and social networks based on our services, which may contain sensitive information such as your personal identity and property, and you have the freedom to choose the shared objects, which means, the third parties that access to your information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">8.2 When you share your personal information with others, social networks, or third-party service providers, or use third-party service links alone or in conjunction with third-party services, you may disclose or enable third parties to obtain your personal information.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">8.3 We recommend that you review the privacy statements of such social networks or third-party service providers to see how they process your information. You shall bear the consequences arising from the provision or sharing of your personal information with others when you use the third-party services, and the corresponding responsible party shall bear the liabilities within the scope prescribed by law.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">8.4 When you share any information publicly on the CASHBOX Wallet software, anyone can potentially view or access that information while using the CASHBOX Wallet platform. The information you voluntarily share when using our services may involve the personal information of you or others. Please make choices carefully and bear your own responsibility.</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>IX. Protection of Minors</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">9.1 We attach great importance to the protection of personal information of minors. According to relevant laws and regulations, if you are a minor under the age of 18, you should obtain the consent of your parent or legal guardian before using the CASHBOX Wallet services. If you are a minor under the age of 14, your guardian should read the Policy carefully and agree that you apply CASHBOX Wallet software in accordance with the Policy.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">9.2 We do not actively collect personal information directly from minors. We will only use, share, transfer or disclose the personal information of minors with the consent of their guardians if permitted by law, agreed by the guardians or necessary to protect the minors.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">9.3 If it is proved that a minor has registered to use our products and/or services without the consent of the guardian, we will consult with the relevant guardian and try to delete the relevant personal information as soon as possible.</span><span class=\"c4\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>X. Scope of Application</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">The Policy applies to all our services. However, certain services have their own specific privacy guidelines/statements that more specifically describe how we process your information in those services. In the event of any inconsistency between the Policy and the privacy guidelines/statements for a particular service, the specific privacy guidelines/statements shall prevail.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Please note that the Policy does not apply to services provided by other companies or individuals. For example, you can log in to a service provided by another company or individual using the CASHBOX Wallet account.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Your use of such third party services is subject to its privacy policy, not the Policy, and you need to read its policy carefully.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">XI. Notification and Revision</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">11.1 The Privacy Policy will be updated as CASHBOX Wallet develops to provide you with a better service. However, we will not abridge your rights under the Privacy Policy without your express consent. We will upload the updated version on the official website and mobile terminal of CASHBOX Wallet, and remind you of the update of relevant content through a website announcement or other appropriate means before it becomes effective. Besides, we ask you to check out the CASHBOX Wallet APP for the latest privacy policy.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">11.2 For significant changes, we will also provide more prominent notifications (we will explain specific changes to the Privacy Policy by including but not limited to emails, text messages or special prompts on browsing pages).</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Significant changes referred to in the Privacy Policy include, but are not limited to:</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">A. Our service model has changed significantly, such as the purpose of processing personal information, the type of personal information processed, and the way to use personal information;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">B. We have experienced significant changes in the ownership structure, organizational structure and other aspects, such as business adjustment, bankruptcy merger and acquisition caused by changes of ownership;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">C. If there are changes in the main object of personal information sharing, transfer or public disclosure;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">D. If your rights to participate in the processing of personal information and mode of execution have changed significantly;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">E. When our department responsible for handling personal information security, contact information and complaint channels change;</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">F. When the assessment report on security impact of personal information indicates a high risk.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">11.3 We will also file the old version of the Privacy Policy for your reference.</span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\"><br>XII. How to Contact Us</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">12.1 If you have any questions, comments or suggestions regarding the Privacy Policy or your personal information, please contact the customer service personnel of CASHBOX Wallet.</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0\"><span class=\"c1\">Email of official customer service:</span><span class=\"c1 c5\">&nbsp;CASHBOX@scry.info</span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p><p class=\"c0 c2\"><span class=\"c1\"></span></p></body></html>";
