  String get service_agreement => "<html><head><meta content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\" http-equiv=\"content-type\"><style type=\"text/css\">@import url('https://themes.googleusercontent.com/fonts/css?kit=wAPX1HepqA24RkYW1AuHYA');ol{margin:0;padding:0}table td,table th{padding:0}.c0{color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";font-style:normal}.c5{color:#000000;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";font-style:normal}.c3{color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\"Calibri\";font-style:normal}.c1{padding-top:0pt;padding-bottom:0pt;line-height:1.0;text-align:justify}.c4{background-color:#ffffff;max-width:415.3pt;padding:72pt 90pt 72pt 90pt}.c2{height:10pt}.title{padding-top:24pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:36pt;padding-bottom:6pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}.subtitle{padding-top:18pt;color:#666666;font-size:24pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:\"Georgia\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;font-style:italic;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}li{color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\"}p{margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\"}h1{padding-top:24pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:24pt;padding-bottom:6pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h2{padding-top:18pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:18pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h3{padding-top:14pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:14pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h4{padding-top:12pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:12pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h5{padding-top:11pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:11pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h6{padding-top:10pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:10pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}</style></head><body class=\"c4\"><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c5\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c5\">CASHBOX Wallet App User Service Agreement</span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">The CASHBOX Wallet App is a mobile digital asset security management service platform (hereinafter referred to as the &quot;platform&quot;) providing the user with digital asset security management services and related services by the Singapore SCRY INFO PRIVATE LTD. The platform provides services to the user who has registered at the platform (hereinafter referred to as the &quot;user&quot;) according to the provisions of this Agreement (as defined below), which is legally binding to both the user and the platform. The platform hereby specially reminds the user to carefully read and fully understand the terms of this Agreement, especially those in this Agreement regarding disclaimer or restriction of liability of the platform, as well as those excluding or restricting the user&rsquo;s rights. The user shall carefully read the instructions, and select to accept or not to accept this Agreement. Unless all terms under this Agreement are accepted by the user, the user has no right to use the services provided by the platform based on this Agreement. If the user disagrees with the contents of this Agreement or refuses to agree the platform&rsquo;s rights to unilaterally alter this Agreement at any time, the user shall immediately stop using and no longer visit the platform. Registration as a user or the use of the services provided by the platform indicates that the user has fully understood and accepted all terms of this Agreement (including any modification made by the Company from time to time).</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">For the convenience of the expression of this Agreement, &quot;we&quot; or other &ldquo;first person&rdquo; are used in this Agreement to indicate the platform in this Agreement; the natural person or other subjects visiting the platform is referred to as &quot;user/ you&quot; or other &ldquo;second person&rdquo;; we and the user are collectively referred to as &quot;parties&quot;, and we or the user are referred to as &quot;either party&quot; in this Agreement.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c3\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Chapter I Definitions and interpretations</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 1 Unless otherwise agreed in the terms of this Agreement, the following words or expressions in this Agreement shall have the following meanings:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(1) This Agreement shall include this service agreement, privacy terms and legal statements, as well as other rules, annexes, statements, instructions or guidelines that have been or will be published on the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(2) Force majeure: including information network equipment maintenance, information network connection failure, computer, communication or other system failures, power failure, unfavorable weathers, accidents, strike, labor disputes, riot, uprising, chaos, insufficient productivity or means of production, fire, flood, storm, explosion, war or other partners&rsquo; causes, digital asset market crash, government behaviors, orders issued by judicial or administrative authorities, and other circumstances beyond the control or out of the control of the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(3) Creation or importing of the Wallet: refers to the process of creating or importing the Wallet using the platform after the user&rsquo;s acceptance of this Agreement.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(4) Affiliated company: a company which has direct or indirect control or significant influence relationship with other companies.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(5) Public key: generated from a private key using one-way derivation method based on the cryptography principle, and used to generate the address of block-chain digital wallet. Digital wallet is the public account collection address.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(6) CASHBOX Wallet (or wallet): a digital asset wallet developed based on the block-chain, including other auxiliary tools developed for the convenience of the user to use the block-chain system.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(7) Wallet password: refers to the password used to encrypt and protect the private key, which shall be decided by the user when creating the wallet. In case of the decentralized application of the CASHBOX Wallet, the wallet password will not be stored in the user&#39;s mobile devices or the platform server. Once the user loses or forgets the password, the user requires to use the private key or mnemonics to set up a new wallet password.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(8) Identity: digital identity generated based on the user&#39;s public and private keys.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(9) User guideline: refers to the guideline provided by the platform to assist the user in understanding the basic knowledge of block-chain and the basic operation procedures of the platform prior to and/ or after the use of the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(10) Private key: composed of 256 random characters, which is vital for the user to own and use digital assets.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(11) Information message: refers to the information message contents showed in the operation interface of the platform. It is recommended that the user should operate according to the relevant steps.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(12) Message center: the in-box in which the user will receive messages or notifications from the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(13) Intellectual property: refers to the definition of Article 92 of this Agreement.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(14) Mnemonics: in line with the Block-chain Industry Standard BIP39, composed of 12 (or 15/ 18/ 21/ 24) words in order generated by the random algorithm method. It is an easy form to record private key, which is convenient for the user for backup and keeping.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 2 Any codes, written decrees or administrative regulations as referred to in this Agreement shall refer to its latest revision, regardless of whether made prior to or after the conclusion of this Agreement.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 3 The title of any clause in this Agreement shall be used for the purpose of convenience, and shall not be used for the purpose of its interpretation. Reference to any statement, clauses</span><a id=\"id.gjdgxs\"></a><span class=\"c0\">, annexes or tables shall mean the reference to the statement, clauses, annexes or tables of this Agreement.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 4 Unless otherwise required in this Agreement, the word &quot;including&quot; as referred to in this Agreement under any circumstances shall mean &quot;including but not limited to&quot;.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 5 Unless otherwise agreed in the terms of this Agreement, in case of any conflict or discrepancy between the documents under this Agreement, the effectiveness of the documents shall be determined in the following order to resolve the conflict or discrepancy in question:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(1) CASHBOX Wallet App User Service Agreement;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(2) CASHBOX Wallet App Privacy Terms;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(3) Other agreements, rules and guidelines.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 6 The user may select to use different language versions of the platform. In case of discrepancy, conflict or omission among different language versions of the platform, the Chinese version of the platform shall prevail.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c3\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Chapter II Basic terms of the platform</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 7 The platform is a digital asset security management service platform. The platform provides services by the Company to the user through platform and client terminal and other ways. The specific services mainly include digital asset security management services, release of digital asset transaction information, user services and other auxiliary services. Please refer to the specific details of the service contents actually provided by the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 8 In order to protect the rights and interests of the user, the user shall carefully read and fully understand all terms of this service agreement prior to the use of platform services voluntarily. The use of platform services shall be deemed as fully understanding and acceptance of this Agreement and any modification made by the platform from time to time; and in case of any legal consequences caused by violations, the user shall independently bear corresponding legal liabilities.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 9 The platform may modify this Agreement according to the circumstances during the performance of this Agreement. Upon the changes in the contents of this Agreement, the platform will publish the latest service agreement, and will not give notice to the user</span><a id=\"id.30j0zll\"></a><span class=\"c0\">&nbsp;individually. If the user disagrees with the modification to this Agreement made by the platform, it has the right to stop using platform services. If the user continues to use platform services, it shall be deemed that the user accepts the modifications to this Agreement made by the platform, and the user shall comply with the modified agreement.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 10 For notices, any other agreement, announcements or other notifications regarding the user&#39;s use of the services sent to the user by the platform, the user agrees that the platform may sent in the form of platform announcement, internal mail, e-mail, mobile phone short message, wireless communication devices and other electronic or physical means, such as mailing. Such notices shall be deemed to have been served to the recipient when sent out (if sent to the user by mail, the notice shall be deemed to be served three natural days after sent to the contact address left by the user in the platform). If the user fails to receive such notices on the date in which the aforesaid notices are deemed to have been served due to the reasons not attributable to the platform (including inaccurate or invalid email address, mobile phone number, contact address, and information transmission failure, etc.), the platform shall not bear any responsibility.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 11 In order to avoid any misoperation of the currency wallet or any security risk of digital token as far as possible, the user shall avoid using the platform without understanding the basic knowledge of block chain. For the user who is not equipped with the basic knowledge of block chain, the Company is entitled to refuse to provide service functions, in whole or in part.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 12 The user understands that the Company will suspend the services (or terminate the service completely in case of the following circumstances):</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(1) The operation of the platform is interrupted due to technical reasons, such as the maintenances, upgrades and failures of equipment and block-chain system, and communication interruption;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(2) The platform fails to provide services due to force majeure and other factors as it reasonably believes that it will cause a greater risk in continuing to provide such services in doing so;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(3) There is a substantially adverse change in the applicable laws or policies; or</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(4) Other circumstances beyond the control of the platform or reasonably foreseen occur.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 13 In case of the changes in the platform, or interruption or termination of the services, the user shall have the right to export the wallet information within a reasonable time limit.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c3\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Chapter 3 Creation of the wallet</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 14 Prior to using platform services, the user shall first create the wallet in the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><a id=\"id.1fob9te\"></a><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 15 The individual user who creates the wallet shall be a natural person who is at least 18 years old or who has full civil rights and capacity for civil conduct according to the laws of the country where the user is located and is able to independently bear civil liabilities.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 16 A legal person, organization or other institution that intends to create the wallet shall designate a natural person who acts as the representative of the organization or institution, and is at least 18 years old or has full civil rights and capacity for civil conduct according to the laws of the country where the user is located.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 17 This Agreement will pop up when the user creates the wallet for the first time. Clicking the &ldquo;Consent&rdquo; button by the user means that the user or the agency legally authorized by the user agrees to all the contents of this Agreement, and the user himself/ herself or the agency authorized by the user is bound by this Agreement. If the user does not have the subject qualification required by Article 15 or Article 16 of this Agreement, the user and the agency which has the right to act as the agent of the user shall bear all the consequences arising therefrom, and the platform shall reserve the right to hold the user and the agency which has the right to act as the agent of the user accountable.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 18 Prior to or after the creation of the wallet, the platform shall have the right to refuse to provide services to the user according to the requirements of laws and regulations, rules, orders and other norms of the country or region where the user is located.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 19 The user hereby undertakes:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(1) The user shall create the wallet and use the platform&rsquo;s services for legitimate purposes, and shall not have the intention of violating laws and regulations by using the platform as a medium;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(2) The user shall guarantee that the digital assets stored in the CASHBOX Wallet are from legal sources;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(3) In addition to this Agreement, the user shall abide by all rules issued and updated by the platform from time to time, including announcement, description for use flow, and risk warning, etc.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 20 If the user violates the commitments it has made in Article 19 of this Agreement:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(1) The platform shall have the right to stop or refuse the user to use partial or all functions of the services provided by it. In this case, the platform shall not bear any responsibility, and the user agrees to bear any direct or indirect expenses or losses arising therefrom;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(2) The user shall bear any direct or indirect losses and adverse consequences caused by the breach of the commitments, and the platform shall reserve the right to hold the user accountable.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 21 The user is willing to use platform services, and the platform does not force, induce, cheat or impose influence on the user by any other unfair means.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c3\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Chapter IV Contents of Registering Platform Services</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 22 The platform shall provide the following services to the user who has completed the registration:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(1) Digital asset security management service;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(2) Information on real-time market conditions and transaction of digital assets;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(3) Digital asset exchange services;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(4) Services provided to the user;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(5) Technical and management services to ensure the normal operation of the platform;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(6) Other services publicized by the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 23 The digital asset security management service mentioned in Article 22 of this Agreement shall include the following contents:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(I) Account importing: the digital assets supported by the CASHBOX Wallet. The user may use the CASHBOX Wallet to generate a new wallet, or import a compatible wallet generated by other wallet tools of the system related to the block-chain.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(II) Transfer and payment collection: the user may manage the digital token using the transfer and payment collection functions of the CASHBOX Wallet, i.e., by electronic signature through the private key to modify the account books of the relevant block-chain. Payment transfer refers to the transfer operation by the payer using the recipient&#39;s ENS domain name or block-chain address. The &quot;transfer&quot; operation involves the effective records of the transactions in the distributed ledger of the relevant block chain system (rather than the actual delivery or transfer of digital token in the CASHBOX).</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(III) Market conditions viewing: the user may use the CASHBOX Wallet to view the exchange rate price of digital token provided by a third party.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(IV) Management of digital token: the user may import, keep or remove other digital asset wallets on the operation interface of the CASHBOX Wallet in addition to the default wallet.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(V) Currency exchange: the user may use the digital asset exchange service provided by the third party. The CASHBOX Wallet is used as the interface tool to assist the user to interact with the third party service provider and to display the corresponding results of digital asset exchange.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(VI) Transaction records: the platform will obtain and display all or partial transaction records of the user from the block-chain, but the user shall refer to the latest transaction records of the block-chain.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(VII) Suspension of services: the platform cannot withdraw or revoke transaction operations for the user due to the &quot;irrevocable&quot; attribute of block-chain transactions. However, in certain circumstances, the platform may suspend or restrict the operations of a certain user on the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">Article 24 Upon the receipt of the services specified in Article 22 of this Agreement, the user agrees and understands:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(I) It shall abide by the decentralized characteristics of the block-chain, and the platform will provide decentralized services, which are different from those provided by banking financial institutions, so as to protect the security of the user&#39;s digital token. The user understands and accepts that the platform does not assume the following responsibilities:</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(1) To store the user&#39;s wallet password (i.e., the password set up when the user creates/ imports the wallet), private key, mnemonics or Keystore;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(2) To retrieve the user&#39;s wallet password, private key, mnemonics or Keystore;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(3) To freeze the wallet;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(4) To report the loss of the wallet;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(5) To recover the wallet;</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(6) To conduct transaction rollback.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(II) The user shall be responsible for taking care of the mobile device containing the currency wallet, backing up CASHBOX Wallet information, wallet password, mnemonics, private key and Keystore. If the mobile device is lost; the CASHBOX Wallet information is deleted or cannot be back up; the wallet is deleted and cannot be back up; the wallet is stolen, or the wallet password, private key, mnemonics or Keystore are forgotten by the user, the platform cannot restore the wallet or retrieve the wallet password, private key, mnemonics or Keystore; and in case of the misoperation in the exchange transaction (such as transferring to the wrong address, and inputting the wrong exchange amount) by the user, the platform neither cancels the transaction, nor bears any responsibility arising therefrom.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(III) The digital token management service provided by the platform does not include the management services of all existing digital assets. It is recommended not to operate any digital assets that are not supported by the platform.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(IV) The currency exchange function provided by the platform is the exchange of digital token in the block-chain system by the user using the third-party smart contract in nature. For the services provided by the third party through smart contract, the platform shall only provide the user with tools to use the third-party smart contract, and shall not provide any guarantee for the functions or service quality of the third-party smart contract. The user shall judge and evaluate whether the services or transactions provided by the third party through smart contract are at risk prior to accepting services or conducting transactions on the third party smart contract. The user shall carefully read and agree to the updated user agreement of relevant smart contracts prior to transactions.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(V) The user understands and agrees to follow the information messages issued by the platform and conducts operations according to the information messages. Otherwise, all risks, responsibilities, losses and expenses arising therefrom shall be borne by the user.</span></p><p class=\"c1 c2\"><span class=\"c0\"></span></p><p class=\"c1\"><span class=\"c0\">(VI) If the platform reasonably believes that the user&#39;s transactions or transaction conditions are abnormal, or the user&#39;s identity information is suspicious, or the platform believes that the user shall submit and verify his/ her identity certificates or other necessary documents, the user shall proactively give cooperation to the platform to check the user&#39;s effective identity certificates or other necessary documents, and complete the relevant identity verifications in a timely manner. The user understands and accepts that the platform may